The Respect for Marriage Act, thanks to the efforts of Majority Leader Schumer, Speaker Pelosi, and bipartisan colleagues, is on its way to becoming a law. The act recognizes same-sex marriages and aims to protect and respect fundamental human rights. It acknowledges the right to start a family, raise children, be open about one's identity, and support loved ones in various situations. The act represents the principle of equality and the belief that all Americans should be treated equally by their government. This is a step closer to achieving that ideal.